Colgate-Palmolive Co said it plans tofile with the Securities and Exchange Commission a shelfregistration covering up to 300 mln dlrs of unsecured debtsecurities.    Reuben Mark, chairman and president of the company, toldthis to a meeting of the New York Society of Security Analysts,Colgate-Palmolive said in a release.    Proceeds will be used for general corporate purposes. Reuter&#3;